HEADWORD: pallbearer
<hw>pall"bear*er</hw> <pr>(p⟦add⟧l"b⟦acir⟧r*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>One of those who attend the coffin at a funeral; -- so called from
the pall being formerly carried by them.</def>⟦br⟧
